Duties: Research, design and test predictive financial modeling systems by using advanced quantitative modeling and statistical analysis skills in the application of computational and analytical principles. Combine market and economic intuition as well sound quantitative analysis/research and data science practices to formulate testable hypotheses about equities markets. Derive data-driven economic hypothesis using advanced economic theory. Apply pattern recognition and statistical analysis techniques, including regression and time-series methods, to formulate and engineer sophisticated quantitative financial modeling systems. Develop production-quality, high-reliability, and highly-tuned code for data ingestion and visualization pipelines. Use knowledge of probability and statistical learning to perform quantitative statistical predictive analysis. Design efficient algorithms for data processing, data visualization, and statistical inference. Build tools to improve the research process of quantitative researchers across the firm. Write detailed reports on quantitative research and tools for management.
Minimum education and experience required: Doctoral Degree (PhD) in Finance, Economics or related financial quantitative field; or in the alternative Master’s Degree in Finance, Economics or related financial quantitative field plus 3 years of experience in a Quantitative Research and Computer Programming type of position(s); or in the alternative Bachelor’s Degree in Finance, Economics or related financial quantitative field plus 5 years of experience in a Quantitative and Computer Programming type of position(s).
Skills required: Must also have knowledge of the following skills:
Ability to program in the context of both an interactive research environment (Python/Jupyter) and in writing lower-level production code (including Java and C++);
Complex, multidimensional data systems;
Software systems including at least three of the following: Linux (operating system), Git (version control), Anaconda (package management), Scikit-learn (machine learning), Apache Spark (data analysis), Pandas (data analysis), Matplotlib (data visualization), and SQL (query language);
In-depth quantitative analysis and the ability to fine-tune/evaluating quantitative models for both theoretical and real-world systems (understanding proper data hygiene as appropriate);
Terabyte-scale data analysis with distributed computing systems, e.g. running and analyzing large-scale computer simulations;
Using statistical inference methods and machine learning techniques as applied in quantitative research, including regression, decision trees, and SVM;
Knowledge of asset pricing and corporate finance theory;
Ability to build mathematical models that target financial and economics systems and knowledge of financial data and balance sheet analysis
Must also pass company’s required skills assessment.

